  "synopsis": "A song for the Minna no Uta segment, it adapts \"Flohwalzer\" (Flea Waltz) is a simple German piano piece, often one of the first learned because its fingering is simple and it allows beginners to perform a piece that is harmonically and rhythmically pleasing. It has different names in different countries but in Japan this piece is known as Neko Funjatta (I Stepped on the Cat).\n\n(Source: Wiki)",
